<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Poland/157</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-08">December 8,
                                        1937</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Polish Ambassador called on no particular business, except to
                                hand me a letter, copy of which is attached,<note n="66" xml:id="d435fn66">Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press
                                        Releases</hi>, December 11, 1937, p. 435.</note> in which
                                the Polish Government declines to make any payment on their
                                debt.</p>
                            <p>The Ambassador incidentally expressed renewed interest in the Jewish
                                problem in Poland and his deep interest in endeavoring to help solve
                                it. He concluded by saying that he believed the acute nature of the
                                problem would subside very soon.</p>
                            <closer><signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>